
## Question statements:

1. Change the main heading 'Fruit Shop' to 'Fruit World'.
2. Change the font color of 'Fruit World' from black to orange.
3. Change the background color of the div with id = "header" to green color.
4. Add a bottom border of orange color to the div with id = "header".
5. Change the font color of 'Fruits In Basket' from black to green.
6. Introduce a paragraph element with text "Please visit us again" inside the div with id = "thanks".

## HTML Code:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body style="margin: 0">
    <div id="header" style="padding: 1rem 0; background-color: lightblue">
      <h1 id="main-heading" style="margin: 0">Fruit Shop</h1>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 id="basket-heading">Fruits In Basket</h2>
      <ul class="fruits">
        <li class="fruit">Banana</li>
        <li class="fruit">Apple</li>
        <li class="fruit">Orange</li>
        <li class="fruit">Kiwi</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div id="thanks"><p>Please visit us again</p></div>
  </body>
  <script src="index.js"></script>
</html>



solutions---------------------------------------------------------------->
// Write your code below:
document.getElementById("main-heading").innerHTML = "Fruit World";
document.getElementById("main-heading").style.color = "orange";
document.getElementById("header").style.backgroundColor = "green";
document.getElementById("header").style.borderBottom = "2px solid orange";
document.getElementById("basket-heading").style.color = "green";


